1
00:00:02,269 --> 00:00:04,638
<i>Just another fried chicken place</i>
<i>in and around Seoul.</i>

2
00:00:05,539 --> 00:00:07,574
<i>The smell of frying oil is strong,</i>

3
00:00:07,641 --> 00:00:09,877
<i>but the sisters' passion is stronger.</i>

4
00:00:13,247 --> 00:00:15,949
<i>It's known as a hangout spot</i>
<i>for various clubs.</i>

5
00:00:16,016 --> 00:00:18,952
HANGANG NAP CONTEST

6
00:00:19,753 --> 00:00:20,754
CHICKEN SISTERS

7
00:00:20,821 --> 00:00:21,722
<i>Pointe.</i>

8
00:00:22,289 --> 00:00:23,357
<i>Pointe.</i>

9
00:00:24,525 --> 00:00:25,492
Pointe.

10
00:00:29,062 --> 00:00:30,364
Is there something going on today?

11
00:00:30,731 --> 00:00:35,969
We're going to be on the cover of
the <i>Monthly Clubs </i>magazine.

12
00:00:40,407 --> 00:00:43,043
We'll make our families proud
by being in this magazine.

13
00:00:43,176 --> 00:00:44,878
You have to be gorgeous
to be on magazine covers.

14
00:00:48,115 --> 00:00:50,584
I'll show you some difficult moves.

15
00:00:50,651 --> 00:00:52,653
I'll show you how to stand on tiptoe.

16
00:00:59,026 --> 00:01:00,460
- Hey.
- Gosh, my calves.

17
00:01:00,994 --> 00:01:03,497
- Hey, you...
- My calves feel like they're bursting.

18
00:01:04,264 --> 00:01:07,367
Did you think
your toes could support your weight?

19
00:01:07,601 --> 00:01:08,502
You can do this, right?

20
00:01:08,569 --> 00:01:11,171
Excuse me. Why are you making me
do moves I can't pull off?

21
00:01:11,238 --> 00:01:12,372
I can't believe this.

22
00:01:12,839 --> 00:01:14,708
Wasn't my ballet turn amazing?

23
00:01:15,008 --> 00:01:17,377
Yes. By the way, are you older than me,
or are we the same age?

24
00:01:17,811 --> 00:01:18,912
- We're of the same age.
- We are?

25
00:01:18,979 --> 00:01:20,080
CHO SU-YEON, MEMBER OF BREATHLESS BALLET
JI YE-EUN, MEMBER OF BREATHLESS BALLET

26
00:01:20,147 --> 00:01:21,148
Are we age-mates?

27
00:01:21,415 --> 00:01:23,317
- You didn't know?
- I just found out.

28
00:01:23,383 --> 00:01:24,851
- Let's just eat fried chicken.
- Let's do that.

29
00:01:24,918 --> 00:01:26,486
I have to watch my weight.

30
00:01:27,454 --> 00:01:28,922
You should straighten your shoulders.

31
00:01:28,989 --> 00:01:31,124
- Hey. You're here.
- They're here.

32
00:01:31,224 --> 00:01:33,994
- Hi.
- Hi, guys.

33
00:01:34,061 --> 00:01:35,862
- Hi.
- Hang on. Why are you all dressed up?

34
00:01:35,929 --> 00:01:37,064
Why do you look so pretty?

35
00:01:37,297 --> 00:01:38,699
- Hey.
- Why are you dressed up?

36
00:01:38,765 --> 00:01:40,601
Ye-eun, this is a bit too much.

37
00:01:40,734 --> 00:01:42,436
Why? I tried to hold myself back.

38
00:01:42,502 --> 00:01:43,637
- Do I look pretty?
- You do.

39
00:01:43,704 --> 00:01:45,105
- You look pretty, but...
- Are you jealous?

40
00:01:45,238 --> 00:01:47,007
It's not like that.

41
00:01:47,074 --> 00:01:49,009
I'm jealous because I don't think
your necklace will fit my neck.

42
00:01:51,278 --> 00:01:53,647
Why are you dressed like Defconn
when we're supposed to do ballet?

43
00:01:53,714 --> 00:01:56,116
What are you talking about?
I'm all dressed up.

44
00:01:56,183 --> 00:01:57,317
- Hang on a second.
- This looks like a shirt for soccer.

45
00:01:57,384 --> 00:01:58,452
- Su-yeon.
- Wait.

46
00:01:58,518 --> 00:02:00,988
Su-yeon, we have to get this straight.

47
00:02:01,054 --> 00:02:02,055
Why are you wearing a ripped one?

48
00:02:02,122 --> 00:02:03,690
I couldn't breathe.

49
00:02:04,091 --> 00:02:05,459
What do we do with this?

50
00:02:05,525 --> 00:02:08,395
Come on, guys,
you should watch your weight!

51
00:02:10,364 --> 00:02:13,734
You should be more respectful.
We're older than you.

52
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:15,802
- We're a lot older than you.
- That's the situation here.

53
00:02:15,869 --> 00:02:17,437
We're older than you in real life too.

54
00:02:17,504 --> 00:02:19,306
- Only you and I are agemates.
- You can't call us like that.

55
00:02:19,373 --> 00:02:21,475
Do you even know where you are now?

56
00:02:23,410 --> 00:02:25,078
- Sorry.
- Do as you please.

57
00:02:25,145 --> 00:02:27,047
I don't mind as long as you swear at us.

58
00:02:27,614 --> 00:02:28,649
It's here.

59
00:02:29,449 --> 00:02:32,019
- Ready or not, rock-paper-scissors.
- Rock-paper-scissors.

60
00:02:32,085 --> 00:02:33,787
- My goodness!
- Yes!

61
00:02:33,854 --> 00:02:34,855
I'm here.

62
00:02:34,921 --> 00:02:35,922
- Hey!
- You're here!

63
00:02:38,325 --> 00:02:41,228
JOO WON
THE ONLY MALE MEMBER OF BREATHLESS BALLET

64
00:02:41,294 --> 00:02:42,396
Won, you're here.

65
00:02:42,996 --> 00:02:44,831
<i>What took you so long? We've been waiting.</i>

66
00:02:44,898 --> 00:02:45,832
<i>There was a bit of traffic</i>
<i>on the way here.</i>

67
00:02:45,899 --> 00:02:46,733
EPISODE 4: BALLET CLUB

68
00:02:47,467 --> 00:02:48,635
Is this when we were 20?

69
00:02:48,702 --> 00:02:49,903
- That's right.
- Twenty years ago?

70
00:02:49,970 --> 00:02:50,804
- Yes.
- When we were 20.

71
00:02:50,871 --> 00:02:52,939
- That's when we first met.
- When we were 20.

72
00:02:53,006 --> 00:02:54,007
We looked so young back then.

73
00:02:54,074 --> 00:02:55,776
- It's been quite a long time.
- We were 20.

74
00:02:55,842 --> 00:02:57,411
- I know.
- We go way back.

75
00:02:57,477 --> 00:02:59,179
By the way, why did you join
the introverted club?

76
00:02:59,246 --> 00:03:01,181
<i>We just pretended to be introverted.</i>

77
00:03:02,249 --> 00:03:03,450
INTROVERTED CLUB

78
00:03:03,517 --> 00:03:05,218
This is Min, our sister.

79
00:03:05,285 --> 00:03:06,486
- Hi, Min.
- Hello.

80
00:03:06,553 --> 00:03:07,688
- My little sister.
- Okay.

81
00:03:07,754 --> 00:03:09,156
- She's...
- I think we met before.

82
00:03:09,222 --> 00:03:11,358
- You did? Where did you see her?
- I guess they met a couple of times.

83
00:03:11,792 --> 00:03:13,326
- Maybe you saw from behind.
- Where did you meet?

84
00:03:13,660 --> 00:03:15,829
- We've known each other for 20 years.
- Right.

85
00:03:15,896 --> 00:03:18,165
She has no interest
in our club activities,

86
00:03:18,231 --> 00:03:19,666
but she seems to be interested in ballet.

87
00:03:19,733 --> 00:03:21,201
She wants to join our club,
Breathless Ballet.

88
00:03:21,268 --> 00:03:22,169
She should join us, then.

89
00:03:24,204 --> 00:03:25,205
Just like that?

90
00:03:26,940 --> 00:03:28,675
I'll just see how things go today.

91
00:03:29,142 --> 00:03:30,544
I'll join you if it looks good.

92
00:03:31,344 --> 00:03:33,146
She usually isn't like this.

93
00:03:33,213 --> 00:03:34,715
- But today...
- I know. Why is she being like that?

94
00:03:34,781 --> 00:03:36,683
- It's not like you.
- It's just...

95
00:03:36,850 --> 00:03:39,086
When you join our club,
you should just focus on ballet.

96
00:03:43,290 --> 00:03:45,158
Hey, why are you picking on my sister?

97
00:03:45,225 --> 00:03:47,060
I'm not picking on her.
This is just how I talk.

98
00:03:47,627 --> 00:03:48,695
You sound really angry now.

99
00:03:48,762 --> 00:03:50,797
I always talk like this.

100
00:03:51,364 --> 00:03:52,666
Why is she so upset?

101
00:03:52,733 --> 00:03:54,468
- I'm not upset. I'm holy.
- Hey.

102
00:03:54,835 --> 00:03:56,269
Where are you trying to go with this?

103
00:03:56,336 --> 00:03:58,438
Hey, don't ruin this for us.

104
00:03:58,505 --> 00:04:00,474
I'm sorry. It's my fault.

105
00:04:01,041 --> 00:04:02,743
We're now the faces of <i>Monthly Clubs.</i>

106
00:04:02,809 --> 00:04:04,277
It's all thanks to Joo Won, isn't it?

107
00:04:04,344 --> 00:04:05,479
- That's right.
- It's nothing.

108
00:04:05,545 --> 00:04:06,613
- I'm so grateful to him.
- You're too kind.

109
00:04:06,680 --> 00:04:07,881
This is what I'm truly grateful for.

110
00:04:08,048 --> 00:04:10,250
Joo Won is busy filming right now.

111
00:04:10,517 --> 00:04:12,819
- He really is.
- And he still took the time to come here.

112
00:04:12,886 --> 00:04:13,954
He's the best.

113
00:04:16,022 --> 00:04:17,624
So, has the filming started yet?

114
00:04:18,291 --> 00:04:19,760
Now, we have...

115
00:04:19,826 --> 00:04:20,827
BEEPING

116
00:04:21,261 --> 00:04:23,096
It's the sound of chicken frying.
Don't mind it.

117
00:04:23,163 --> 00:04:24,131
- Just ignore it.
- It's the chicken.

118
00:04:24,197 --> 00:04:26,133
- It's being fried.
- We have about ten days left.

119
00:04:26,199 --> 00:04:28,268
- For what?
- Until the filming starts.

120
00:04:28,335 --> 00:04:29,336
What are you filming?

121
00:04:29,402 --> 00:04:31,037
- It's called <i>The Sword.</i>
<i>- The Sword?</i>

122
00:04:31,104 --> 00:04:32,239
It's a historical action film.

123
00:04:32,305 --> 00:04:33,807
- A historical action film?
- A historical action film!

124
00:04:33,874 --> 00:04:34,775
<i>The Sword!</i>

125
00:04:34,841 --> 00:04:36,476
- By the director of <i>Roaring Currents.</i>
- That's right.

126
00:04:36,576 --> 00:04:37,544
Kim Han...

127
00:04:37,611 --> 00:04:39,079
- Director Kim Han-min.
- Director Kim Han-min.

128
00:04:39,146 --> 00:04:40,847
- My goodness. This is...
- Director Kim Han-min?

129
00:04:41,014 --> 00:04:42,549
- What role do you play?
- I'm a warrior.

130
00:04:42,616 --> 00:04:45,218
- Awesome.
- My gosh. I love warriors.

131
00:04:46,953 --> 00:04:48,855
Wasn't it difficult learning
martial arts and all that?

132
00:04:49,189 --> 00:04:50,023
It is difficult.

133
00:04:50,090 --> 00:04:52,526
- I imagine it would be.
- And I have to use two swords.

134
00:04:52,692 --> 00:04:54,227
- I have to use both hands.
- Really?

135
00:04:54,294 --> 00:04:56,963
Using my right hand feels natural,

136
00:04:57,030 --> 00:04:59,399
- Your left hand?
- but I'm not good at using my left hand.

137
00:04:59,466 --> 00:05:00,700
- Right.
- That's what I'm working on now.

138
00:05:00,767 --> 00:05:03,170
Do you do the action scenes yourself
without a stunt double?

139
00:05:03,436 --> 00:05:05,806
I'm trying to do everything myself
if possible.

140
00:05:05,872 --> 00:05:07,541
- That's so cool.
- But for scenes that are too dangerous,

141
00:05:07,607 --> 00:05:10,310
we'll have to let
the stunt team handle them.

142
00:05:10,610 --> 00:05:12,779
I can't wait to watch it, Won!

143
00:05:13,413 --> 00:05:14,548
You should come and watch it.

144
00:05:14,614 --> 00:05:15,749
- We will!
- Can you show us

145
00:05:15,816 --> 00:05:17,217
- the sword fight here?
- What?

146
00:05:17,284 --> 00:05:18,919
- Can you show us a little here?
- The sword fight?

147
00:05:18,985 --> 00:05:20,453
- Show us!
- Show us!

148
00:05:20,520 --> 00:05:21,521
- Show us!
- Show us!

149
00:05:21,588 --> 00:05:22,856
- How can I...
- Show us!

150
00:05:22,923 --> 00:05:25,325
- There's nothing to show.
- Let's do this then.

151
00:05:25,392 --> 00:05:26,793
- Using this...
- No way.

152
00:05:27,928 --> 00:05:28,929
Use this.

153
00:05:29,563 --> 00:05:32,632
- Think of this as a sword.
- Are you serious?

154
00:05:32,766 --> 00:05:34,734
Try stabbing Ye-eun with it.

155
00:05:34,868 --> 00:05:36,503
I think you'd be perfect for that, Sun-ja.

156
00:05:36,570 --> 00:05:38,071
You're good at taking a hit.

157
00:05:38,505 --> 00:05:41,908
If you get annoyed,
it's okay to stab her for real.

158
00:05:41,975 --> 00:05:43,009
But Sun-ja...

159
00:05:43,076 --> 00:05:44,744
Sun-ja can take a hit.

160
00:05:44,811 --> 00:05:46,780
- But if you just stab Sun-ja like this...
- What?

161
00:05:46,847 --> 00:05:48,548
- It...
- Do you think she will bounce off?

162
00:05:48,748 --> 00:05:49,850
It won't go all the way in.

163
00:05:50,083 --> 00:05:52,986
Hang on. What's that supposed to mean?

164
00:05:53,053 --> 00:05:54,054
- What do you mean?
- The thing is...

165
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:55,355
This is just fat.

166
00:05:55,422 --> 00:05:57,157
- It won't go all the way in?
- The sword is too short.

167
00:05:57,224 --> 00:05:58,291
- Is that so?
- Right.

168
00:05:58,358 --> 00:06:00,260
- When you use two swords with both hands,
- Yes?

169
00:06:00,327 --> 00:06:02,462
one is for defense,
and the other is for attack.

170
00:06:02,529 --> 00:06:03,697
- I see.
- Really?

171
00:06:04,164 --> 00:06:06,466
Let's say you're attacking me
with a sword this way.

172
00:06:06,533 --> 00:06:08,401
Then I sit down like this
and slash it away.

173
00:06:09,035 --> 00:06:11,338
And I cut you with the sword like this.

174
00:06:13,640 --> 00:06:15,542
- That's so cool.
- That's cool.

175
00:06:15,609 --> 00:06:17,777
Then I block the attack with a sword.

176
00:06:18,211 --> 00:06:19,713
I block it and kick her.

177
00:06:19,913 --> 00:06:21,348
- I see.
- And then...

178
00:06:22,048 --> 00:06:23,984
- He's really good.
- And...

179
00:06:24,384 --> 00:06:25,485
He's really good.

180
00:06:25,552 --> 00:06:28,088
And I stab her like this.

181
00:06:29,489 --> 00:06:30,991
That looks cool!

182
00:06:31,091 --> 00:06:34,060
I usually hold a sword like this,
but I change the direction of my grip.

183
00:06:36,663 --> 00:06:38,331
Sun-ja should star in the film too.

184
00:06:39,332 --> 00:06:40,734
I dodge it and kick.

185
00:06:41,668 --> 00:06:43,303
- My goodness.
- Then I go like this.

186
00:06:43,370 --> 00:06:45,505
Sometimes another bad guy appears
behind you like this.

187
00:06:46,973 --> 00:06:48,108
- I dodge it like this.
- Just as the bad guy appears...

188
00:06:49,242 --> 00:06:50,343
And I stab you like this.

189
00:06:52,112 --> 00:06:54,614
- That's so cool.
- He looks so awesome.

190
00:07:07,560 --> 00:07:09,996
- That's not it.
- Here you go.

191
00:07:11,164 --> 00:07:12,299
Nice!

192
00:07:14,167 --> 00:07:15,535
Nice!

193
00:07:15,602 --> 00:07:17,037
Can we really eat this fried chicken?

194
00:07:17,103 --> 00:07:18,338
- Yes, we can.
- Sure.

195
00:07:18,405 --> 00:07:19,639
It's not a prop.

196
00:07:20,607 --> 00:07:22,208
Did Min fry this?

197
00:07:22,275 --> 00:07:23,276
Yes, she did.

198
00:07:23,343 --> 00:07:25,278
- Enjoy it.
- Min is good at this.

199
00:07:25,345 --> 00:07:27,280
- Frying chicken is her job.
- I see.

200
00:07:27,447 --> 00:07:28,915
Which piece do you want, Won?

201
00:07:29,115 --> 00:07:30,617
I like chicken breast.

202
00:07:32,085 --> 00:07:33,887
Is that something to shout about?

203
00:07:35,121 --> 00:07:37,123
Is that something to shout about?

204
00:07:37,524 --> 00:07:39,926
- Why is she shouting?
- Hang on. Come on out.

205
00:07:40,293 --> 00:07:41,328
Follow me.

206
00:07:41,394 --> 00:07:43,063
Cut it out or you'll be sorry.

207
00:07:43,530 --> 00:07:44,698
- Enough.
- Okay.

208
00:07:44,831 --> 00:07:48,168
- I'm really scared of Sun-ja.
- Really?

209
00:07:48,234 --> 00:07:51,071
- Is this okay? Can Sun-ja really do this?
- She can.

210
00:07:51,171 --> 00:07:54,140
Hang on.
Who in the world speaks like that?

211
00:07:54,374 --> 00:07:55,809
You sound totally mad.

212
00:07:56,443 --> 00:07:57,277
- Let's have a toast.
- Let's do that.

213
00:07:57,544 --> 00:07:58,678
It's nice to see you. Breathless!

214
00:07:58,745 --> 00:08:01,281
- Ballet! This is great.
- Ballet!

215
00:08:03,984 --> 00:08:05,685
This is good, and this...

216
00:08:05,752 --> 00:08:07,554
It's what we call
old-fashioned fried chicken.

217
00:08:07,620 --> 00:08:08,888
That's right.
We have the best fried chicken.

218
00:08:08,955 --> 00:08:11,191
Min does all the research
and fries the chicken herself.

219
00:08:11,257 --> 00:08:12,492
I do.

220
00:08:13,026 --> 00:08:14,561
- Do you like it?
- Look at this.

221
00:08:18,231 --> 00:08:20,000
- Min, this is so good.
- It is.

222
00:08:20,066 --> 00:08:22,268
- It's really crispy.
- It is.

223
00:08:22,335 --> 00:08:23,236
It's still warm too.

224
00:08:23,303 --> 00:08:25,171
- Eat up, everyone.
- It's so good.

225
00:08:25,572 --> 00:08:27,474
These days,
you don't usually go to the restaurant

226
00:08:27,707 --> 00:08:29,409
to have fried chicken.

227
00:08:29,476 --> 00:08:30,977
- You're right.
- This is so good.

228
00:08:31,044 --> 00:08:33,446
- We usually order in.
- I know. And it gets cold.

229
00:08:33,513 --> 00:08:36,149
You can eat it at a restaurant
thanks to our ballet club.

230
00:08:36,249 --> 00:08:38,184
If it weren't for Breathless Ballet,
we wouldn't be able to enjoy this.

231
00:08:38,251 --> 00:08:41,688
So, who else is in the TV drama
besides you?

232
00:08:42,055 --> 00:08:43,089
- It's a film.
- I thought...

233
00:08:44,624 --> 00:08:45,759
- I'm sorry.
- It's a film.

234
00:08:45,825 --> 00:08:47,927
- Sun-i is quite slow.
- Hey!

235
00:08:47,994 --> 00:08:49,429
Hey! Come on!

236
00:08:49,496 --> 00:08:50,630
- I'm sorry.
- It's no big deal.

237
00:08:50,697 --> 00:08:52,665
- We even mentioned <i>Roaring Currents.</i>
- We did.

238
00:08:52,732 --> 00:08:55,035
The director of the film
is making <i>The Sword,</i> right?

239
00:08:55,101 --> 00:08:56,836
Park Bo-gum will be in it too.

240
00:08:58,304 --> 00:08:59,172
Park Bo-gum.

241
00:09:00,907 --> 00:09:01,941
Park Bo-gum.

242
