She refused.

978
00:36:33,024 --> 00:36:34,993
But I can take care of you.

979
00:36:35,360 --> 00:36:37,128
But I can take care of you.

980
00:36:37,762 --> 00:36:38,830
I'd love that.

981
00:36:39,531 --> 00:36:40,498
Hang on.

982
00:36:40,965 --> 00:36:42,567
Hang on.

983
00:36:42,634 --> 00:36:44,803
- You can't change your mind so quickly.
- You should let him be cute.

984
00:36:44,869 --> 00:36:46,204
You should let him be cute.

985
00:36:46,271 --> 00:36:48,406
How could you fall for that right away?

986
00:36:48,473 --> 00:36:49,974
You should try hearing it from here.

987
00:36:50,675 --> 00:36:51,576
You have to try.

988
00:36:51,643 --> 00:36:53,078
- His voice is so romantic, right?
- Yes.

989
00:36:53,144 --> 00:36:54,713
But you should keep insisting.

990
00:36:54,779 --> 00:36:57,682
"I don't want to.
I'm really tired and want to go home."

991
00:36:57,749 --> 00:37:00,185
And that's when you'd show us
your ultimate move.

992
00:37:00,251 --> 00:37:01,486
- My ultimate move?
- Yes.

993
00:37:06,357 --> 00:37:07,959
She'd love that!

994
00:37:09,360 --> 00:37:10,995
This is too much!

995
00:37:13,164 --> 00:37:14,265
She'd love that!

996
00:37:14,332 --> 00:37:16,000
This is too much!

997
00:37:23,475 --> 00:37:25,210
Hey! Hurry and go over there!

998
00:37:25,276 --> 00:37:27,212
- Hurry over.
- I'm going.

999
00:37:27,278 --> 00:37:28,646
You should go with him.

1000
00:37:28,947 --> 00:37:31,449
- That was really insane.
- He's so good at it.

1001
00:37:31,516 --> 00:37:34,018
- He really is.
- Impressive.

1002
00:37:34,185 --> 00:37:36,354
- I'm falling for him.
- Me too.

1003
00:37:36,955 --> 00:37:38,189
- You know what?
- What?

1004
00:37:38,256 --> 00:37:40,825
If we got him 1,000ml of water here,
he'd do this all day.

1005
00:37:40,892 --> 00:37:41,760
He will.

1006
00:37:41,826 --> 00:37:44,696
- I just need to wet my lips.
- As long as we have a water purifier.

1007
00:37:44,763 --> 00:37:47,198
- He can do this all night.
- He can do it all night.

1008
00:37:48,399 --> 00:37:49,601
That was fun.

1009
00:37:49,768 --> 00:37:51,903
- So we tried role-playing.
- Right.

1010
00:37:51,970 --> 00:37:54,906
And I can tell that he's quite flexible
when he's in a relationship...

1011
00:37:54,973 --> 00:37:56,074
Kind of like banter, right?

1012
00:37:56,141 --> 00:37:57,742
- He's good at playing along with jokes.
- That's true.

1013
00:37:57,809 --> 00:37:59,844
So I'm sure about this.

1014
00:37:59,944 --> 00:38:00,979
About what?

1015
00:38:01,746 --> 00:38:02,680
About what?

1016
00:38:03,515 --> 00:38:04,849
- About what?
- You're seeing someone, aren't you?

1017
00:38:08,186 --> 00:38:09,821
Really? Is that true?

1018
00:38:12,757 --> 00:38:13,825
Are we going to reveal it here?

1019
00:38:14,392 --> 00:38:16,828
What? What are you saying?

1020
00:38:17,362 --> 00:38:19,330
- What?
- What is it now?

1021
00:38:19,397 --> 00:38:20,832
Are you acting or what?

1022
00:38:22,500 --> 00:38:23,468
I was acting.

1023
00:38:23,535 --> 00:38:25,170
You surprised me just now.

1024
00:38:25,236 --> 00:38:26,437
You're not seeing anyone right now?

1025
00:38:26,504 --> 00:38:27,539
- I'm not.
- Really?

1026
00:38:27,605 --> 00:38:28,673
- Really?
- I'm not.

1027
00:38:28,740 --> 00:38:30,475
That's too bad.

1028
00:38:30,542 --> 00:38:31,843
Do you want to get married?

1029
00:38:31,910 --> 00:38:33,144
- Of course.
- Really?

1030
00:38:33,211 --> 00:38:34,345
When do you want to get married?

1031
00:38:34,946 --> 00:38:36,848
I'm already past the point
where I wanted to get married.

1032
00:38:36,915 --> 00:38:39,350
- Really?
- I wanted to get married in my late 30s.

1033
00:38:39,617 --> 00:38:41,519
I'm already past that age.

1034
00:38:41,953 --> 00:38:45,990
Maybe I should
try to get married as soon as possible.

1035
00:38:46,524 --> 00:38:48,760
I don't think it's a good idea
to get married too late.

1036
00:38:48,827 --> 00:38:50,595
- That's true.
- Do you want to marry an actress

1037
00:38:50,662 --> 00:38:51,629
or someone of a different profession?

1038
00:38:51,696 --> 00:38:53,932
- That doesn't matter.
- It doesn't matter?

1039
00:38:53,998 --> 00:38:56,534
You just want someone chubby and tough?

1040
00:38:56,801 --> 00:38:59,270
It would be nice to meet
a chubby, tough woman.

1041
00:38:59,604 --> 00:39:00,572
- Yes.
- I see.

1042
00:39:01,039 --> 00:39:03,675
Many people have
small weddings these days.

1043
00:39:03,741 --> 00:39:05,710
The bride and groom even sing
a congratulatory song at their wedding.

1044
00:39:05,777 --> 00:39:06,811
- Right.
- Right.

1045
00:39:06,878 --> 00:39:11,182
Is there a song you'd like to sing
for your bride at the wedding?

1046
00:39:11,916 --> 00:39:13,084
- A song?
- Yes.

1047
00:39:14,686 --> 00:39:16,955
- Won is a great singer.
- My gosh!

1048
00:39:17,422 --> 00:39:18,823
He sings so well.

1049
00:39:18,890 --> 00:39:20,491
- Show us!
- Show us!

1050
00:39:20,558 --> 00:39:21,860
- Show us!
- Show us!

1051
00:39:21,926 --> 00:39:24,195
- He also did musicals.
- Show us.

1052
00:39:24,829 --> 00:39:25,730
Okay.

1053
00:39:31,703 --> 00:39:35,673
<i>Would I be able to smile without you?</i>

1054
00:39:36,241 --> 00:39:40,211
<i>Would I be able to smile without you?</i>

1055
00:39:42,647 --> 00:39:47,352
<i>Just the thought of it</i>
<i>Brings tears to my eyes</i>

1056
00:39:48,052 --> 00:39:51,956
<i>You were there for me during hard times</i>

1057
00:39:53,258 --> 00:39:58,096
<i>Now I'll be there to protect you</i>

1058
00:39:59,063 --> 00:40:02,867
<i>Your embrace was always warm</i>

1059
00:40:03,501 --> 00:40:07,205
<i>The only shelter I had</i>

1060
00:40:07,272 --> 00:40:10,074
<i>At the end of a long day</i>

1061
00:40:11,376 --> 00:40:17,148
<i>I only need you</i>

1062
00:40:17,582 --> 00:40:20,818
<i>Even just a glance is enough</i>

1063
00:40:20,885 --> 00:40:23,955
<i>To know how we feel</i>

1064
00:40:25,490 --> 00:40:29,360
<i>Let's be together every day, every moment</i>

1065
00:40:29,761 --> 00:40:34,565
<i>A single flower blooms and withers</i>

1066
00:40:34,666 --> 00:40:37,268
- That was the song.
- He sings so well.

1067
00:40:37,335 --> 00:40:38,303
That was amazing.

1068
00:40:38,369 --> 00:40:40,905
Let's stay together
every day, every moment.

1069
00:40:40,972 --> 00:40:43,141
- He's so talented.
- He's the best.

1070
00:40:43,207 --> 00:40:45,076
How could your voice be so sweet?

1071
00:40:45,276 --> 00:40:46,978
It's really sad to part ways like this.

1072
